text.tspan: Survival ages across the population, France, 1816 to 2023
The number of years that a specific share of the population would survive, if they were born in a given year and
experienced age-specific death rates of that year. For example, the line indicating 1% corresponds to the top
1% of survivors born in a given year and the number of years of their survival.
Data source: Alvarez & Vaupel (2023); Human Mortality Database (2025)
